The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the sparsest cut problem on graphs with a specific expansion property, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques and combinatorial algorithms, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the algorithm to graphs with genus, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and may fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
